cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper deals with formalizing and proving the secrecy of protocols, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Isabelle, a proof assistant, suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO) or programming languages (cs.PL). The application of the protocol-independent secrecy theorem to e-commerce protocols suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) or software engineering (cs.SE).
